value.value: CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that produces IL-22.

definition.value: TH22 cells are also reportedly CCR4-positive, CCR6-positive, CCR10-positive, CXCR3-negative. TH22 cells are reportedly capable of secreting IL-13.

label.value: activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell, human

value.value: A recently activated CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD38-positive, CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, and CD25-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'activated CD4+ T cell', but includes via logical inference from its parent additional markers known to be expressed on activated CD4+ T cells.  The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human activated CD4+ T cells, as activated mouse T cells do not express MHC class II.

value.value: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'effector CD4+ T cell'.  The functional characteristics of this cell type currently undefined in CL, which affects its proper placement within the hierarchy.

value.value: A naive regulatory T cell with the phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'naive CCR4+ Treg'.  The definition is valid for human; its applicability for mouse and other species is unknown.

value.value: A memory regulatory T cell with phenotype CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CD127lo, CCR4-positive, and CD45RO-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'memory CCR4+ Treg'.  The definition is valid for human; its applicability for mouse and other species is unknown.

label.value: CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CCR4-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell

value.value: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell with the additional phenotype CCR4-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'CCR4+ Treg'.  The definition is valid for human; its applicability for mouse and other species is unknown.

label.value: activated CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CCR4-positive, alpha-beta regulatory T cell, human

value.value: A CD4-positive, CD25-positive, CCR4-positive, alpha-beta T regulatory cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, indicating recent activation.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'activated CCR4+ Treg'.  The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human activated CD4+ T cells, as activated mouse T cells do not express MHC class II.

label.value: activated CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell, human

value.value: A recently activated CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD38-positive, CD69-positive, CD62L-negative, CD127-negative, CCR7-negative, and CD25-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'activated CD8+ T cell', but includes via logical inference from its parent additional markers known to be expressed on activated CD8+ T cells.  The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human activated CD8+ T cells, as activated mouse T cells do not express MHC class II.

value.value: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with the phenotype CCR7-negative, CD45RA-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'effector CD8+ T cell'.  The functional characteristics of this cell type currently undefined in CL, which affects its proper placement within the hierarchy.

label.value: CD4-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative, alpha-beta T cell

value.value: A CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'non-Th1/Th17 CD4+ T cell'.  Cells of this phenotype may include T-helper 2 T cells and some naive CD4+ T cells.

label.value: CD8-positive, CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative, alpha-beta T cell

value.value: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell that has the phenotype CXCR3-negative, CCR6-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'non-Tc1/Tc17 CD8+ T cell'.  Cells of this phenotype may include Tc2 T cells and some naive CD8+ T cells.

value.value: A memory B cell that lacks expression of surface IgD.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'IgD- memory B cell'.  The majority of these cells are class-switched, though some are IgM-positive.

value.value: A monocyte that expresses CD14 and is negative for the lineage markers CD3, CD19, and CD20.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'monocyte'. Note that while CD14 is considered a reliable marker for human monocytes, it is only expressed on approximately 85% of mouse monocytes.

value.value: An intermediate monocyte that is CD14-positive and with low amounts of CD16.

definition.value: Definition is valid for human intermediate monocytes.

value.value: A dendritic cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'dendritic cell'. The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human dendritic cells.

value.value: A myeloid dendritic cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'myeloid dendritic cell'. The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human myeloid dendritic cells.

value.value: A plasmacytoid dendritic cell with the phenotype HLA-DRA-positive, CD123-positive, and CD11c-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is compatible with the HIPC Lyoplate markers for 'plasmacytoid dendritic cell'. The inclusion of HLA-DRA in the definition restricts this definition to human plasmacytoid dendritic cells.

value.value: A progenitor cell committed to myeloid lineage, including the megakaryocyte and erythroid lineages. These cells are CD34-positive, and express Gata1, Gata2, C/EBPa, and Pu.1.

definition.value: CMP are reportedly CD16-positive, CD32-positive, CD38-positive, CD45RA-negative, CD110-negative, CD117-positive, CD123-positive, and SCA1-negative.

value.value: A hematopoietic oligopotent progenitor cell that has the ability to differentiate into limited cell types but lacks lineage cell markers and self renewal capabilities. Cell lacks hematopoeitic lineage markers.

A cell found in an organism or derived from an organism exhibiting a phenotype that deviates from the expected phenotype of any native cell type of that organism. Abnormal cells are typically found in disease states or disease models.

definition.value: https://github.com/obophenotype/cell-ontology/issues/448

label.value: effector memory CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell, terminally differentiated

value.value: A CD8-positive, alpha beta memory T cell with the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is seen in human but not found in the mouse.

value.value: An abnormal cell exhibiting dysregulation of cell proliferation or programmed cell death and capable of forming a neoplasm, an aggregate of cells in the form of a tumor mass or an excess number of abnormal cells (liquid tumor) within an organism.

definition.value: https://github.com/obophenotype/cell-ontology/issues/448

value.value: A neoplastic cell that is capable of entering a surrounding tissue

definition.value: https://github.com/obophenotype/cell-ontology/issues/448

value.value: A lymphocyte that lacks characteristic T cell, B cell, myeloid cell, and dendritic cell markers, that functions as part of the innate immune response to produce cytokines and other effector responses.
A progenitor cell committed to the erythroid lineage. This cell is ter119-positive but lacks expression of other hematopoietic lineage markers (lin-negative).
An innate lymphoid cell that is capable of producing the type 1 cytokine IFN-gamma, but not Th2 or Th17 cell-associated cytokines.
A group 1 innate lymphoid cell that is non-cytotoxic.
An innate lymphoid cell that is capable of producing T-helper 2-cell associated cytokines upon stimulation.
An adipocyte that is beige in color, thermogenic, and which differentiates in white fat tissue from a Myf5-negative progenitor.
An innate lymphoid cell that constituitively expresses RORgt and is capable of expressing IL17A and/or IL-22.

label.value: CD34-negative, CD117-positive innate lymphoid cell, human

value.value: An innate lymphoid cell in the human with the phenotype CD34-negative, CD117-positive, and a precusor to NK cells, ILC2 cells, and ILC3 cells.

label.value: CD34-negative, CD56-positive, CD117-positive innate lymphoid cell, human

value.value: An innate lymphoid cell in the human with the phenotype CD34-negative, CD56-positive, CD117-positive.Thie cell type may include precusors to NK cells and ILC3 cells.

label.value: CD34-positive, CD56-positive, CD117-positive common innate lymphoid precursor, human

value.value: An innate lymphoid cell precursor in the human with the phenotype CD34-positive, CD56-positive, CD117-positive.Thie cell type may include precusors to NK cells and ILC3 cells.
An innate lymphoid cell in the human with the phenotype KLRG1-positive that is a precusor for ILC2 cells.
An innate lymphoid cell in the human with the phenotype NKp46-positive that is a precusor for NK cells and ILC3 cells.
An ILC1 cell in the human with the phenotype CD56-negative, IL-7Ralpha-positive, T-bet-positive.
A group 3 innate lymphoid cell in the human with the phenotype IL-7Ralpha-positive.

label.value: NKp44-positive group 3 innate lymphoid cell, human

value.value: A group 3 innate lymphoid cell in the human with the phenotype IL-7Ralpha-positive, and NKp44-positive.

label.value: NKp44-negative group 3 innate lymphoid cell, human

value.value: A group 3 innate lymphoid cell in the human with the phenotype IL-7Ralpha-positive, and NKp44-negative.
A group 2 innate lymphoid cell in the human with the phenotype CD25-positive, CD127-positive, CD161-positive, and GATA-3-positive.
An innate lyphoid cell with an immature phenotype.

label.value: effector memory CD4-positive, alpha-beta T cell, terminally differentiated

value.value: A CD4-positive, alpha beta memory T cell with the phenotype CD45RA-positive, CD45RO-negative, and CCR7-negative.

definition.value: This cell type is seen in human but not found in the mouse.

value.value: A lymphocyte of B lineage that is CD19-positive.

definition.value: Types of B lineage lymphocytes include B cells and antibody secreting cells (plasmablasts and plasma cells).  Lymphocytes of B cell lineage can be distinguished from those of T cell lineage by their lack of CD3e (as part of the T cell receptor complex).

value.value: A B cell that is CD19-positive.
A plasmablast that is CD86-positive.

label.value: CD8-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell, CD45RO-positive

value.value: A CD8-positive, alpha-beta T cell with memory phenotype indicated by being CD45RO and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label.value: CD4-positive, alpha-beta memory T cell, CD45RO-positive

value.value: CD4-positive, alpha-beta long-lived T cell with the phenotype CD45RO-positive and CD127-positive. This cell type is also described as being CD25-negative, CD44-high, and CD122-high.

label.value: visual pigment cell (sensu Nematoda and Protostomia)

value.value: An erythroid progenitor cell is Kit-positive, Ly6A-negative, CD41-negative, CD127-negative, and CD123-negative. This cell type is also described as being lin-negative, Kit-positive, CD150-negative, CD41-negative, CD105-positive, and FcgR-negative.

definition.value: Markers found on mouse cells.

value.value: A granulocyte monocyte progenitor is CD34-positive, CD38-positive, IL-3receptor-alpha-positive and is CD45RA-negative.

definition.value: Markers are for human cells. According to different research groups, CD45RA is present or absent on this cell population.
